<paragraph id="1B2F252ACE3802036DD0FD866486333E" blockId="2.[132,681,568,816]" pageId="2" pageNumber="83">
<emphasis id="29E4F938CE3802036DD0FD866774325E" box="[132,340,568,592]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="83">
Discussão: 
<taxonomicName id="DC905EA9CE3802036DBFFD876774325E" authority="Curletti &amp; Migliore, 2014" authorityName="Curletti &amp; Migliore" authorityYear="2014" box="[235,340,568,592]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Agrilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aegrotus" status="sp. nov.">A. aegrotus</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="32D74443CE3802036C0EFD8767873241" box="[346,423,568,591]" pageId="2" pageNumber="83" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
também pertence ao grupo de 
<taxonomicName id="DC905EA9CE3802036D91FDE7671C327E" authority="Curletti &amp; Migliore, 2014" authorityName="Curletti &amp; Migliore" authorityYear="2014" box="[197,316,600,624]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Agrilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="timorosus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="29E4F938CE3802036D91FDE7671C327E" box="[197,316,600,624]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="83">A. timorosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="32D74443CE3802036C10FDE767B13261" box="[324,401,600,623]" pageId="2" pageNumber="83" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
Todavia, devido às suas pequenas dimensões (menos de 
<quantity id="DC6888CFCE3802036CFEFDC767C8329E" box="[426,488,632,656]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="83" unit="mm" value="5.0">5 mm</quantity>
) na fauna brasileira pode ser comparado a 
<taxonomicName id="DC905EA9CE3802036C22FD27648932BE" authority="Kerremans, 1897" authorityName="Kerremans" authorityYear="1897" box="[374,681,664,688]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Agrilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="villosulus">
<emphasis id="29E4F938CE3802036C22FD2767CD32BE" box="[374,493,664,688]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="83">A. villosulus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="7F0158DBCE3802036CA3FD27648932BE" author="KERREMANS, C." box="[503,681,664,688]" pageId="2" pageNumber="83" pagination="1 - 146" refId="ref15132" refString="KERREMANS, C. 1897. Contribution a l'etude de la faune intertropicale Americaine. Voyages de M. E. Gounelle au Bresil. Buprestides. Memoires de la Societe entomologique de Belgique, 6: 1 - 146." type="journal article" year="1897">Kerremans, 1897</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
descrito de 
<collectingRegion id="D954EBC8CE3802036DA7FD07675132DE" box="[243,369,696,720]" country="Brazil" name="Pernambuco" pageId="2" pageNumber="83">Pernambuco</collectingRegion>
e a 
<taxonomicName id="DC905EA9CE3802036CC1FD07648932DE" authority="Kerremans, 1897" authorityName="Kerremans" authorityYear="1897" box="[405,681,696,720]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Agrilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ignavus">
<emphasis id="29E4F938CE3802036CC1FD0767D832DE" box="[405,504,696,720]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="83">A. ignavus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="7F0158DBCE3802036CA9FD07648932DE" author="KERREMANS, C." box="[509,681,696,720]" pageId="2" pageNumber="83" pagination="1 - 146" refId="ref15132" refString="KERREMANS, C. 1897. Contribution a l'etude de la faune intertropicale Americaine. Voyages de M. E. Gounelle au Bresil. Buprestides. Memoires de la Societe entomologique de Belgique, 6: 1 - 146." type="journal article" year="1897">Kerremans, 1897</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
de 
<collectingRegion id="D954EBC8CE3802036DF5FD6766FE32FE" box="[161,222,728,752]" country="Brazil" name="Goias" pageId="2" pageNumber="83">Goiás</collectingRegion>
. O primeiro diferencia-se por possuir o pronoto mais alongado com os lados regularmente arredondados, o segundo por possuir a carena pré-umeral inteira.
</paragraph>
